Q. The current population of a town is 10000. The population of the town is increasing at the rate of 10% per year. You have to write a program to find out the population at the end of each of the last 10 years. For egcurrent population is 10000 so the output should be like this:
     10th year - 10000
     9th year - 9000
     8th year - 8100 and so on
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:

def fun(population):    
    increase_in_population=population*0.1
    for i in range(10,0,-1):       
        print(i,"th year -",int(population))
        population=population-increase_in_population
        
population=int(input("enter the population of the town:"))
fun(population)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

enter the population of the town: 10000
10 th year - 10000
9 th year - 9000
8 th year - 8000
7 th year - 7000
6 th year - 6000
5 th year - 5000
4 th year - 4000
3 th year - 3000
2 th year - 2000
1 th year - 1000
